{"title_page": "Love Will Turn You Around", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Love Will Turn You Around\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Kenny Rogers]]\n| cover      = Love Will Turn You Around.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1982\n| recorded   = 1982\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Country music|Country]]\n| length     = 32:00\n| label      = [[Liberty Records|Liberty]]\n| producer   = Kenny Rogers, [[David Malloy]], [[Brent Maher]], [[Randy Goodrum]], [[Val Garay]]\n| prev_title = [[Christmas (Kenny Rogers album)|Christmas]]\n| prev_year  = 1981\n| next_title = [[We've Got Tonight (Kenny Rogers album)|We've Got Tonight]]\n| next_year  = 1983\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Love Will Turn You Around\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Love Will Turn You Around (song)|Love Will Turn You Around]]\n | single1date = June 28, 1982\n | single2     = [[A Love Song (Lee Greenwood song)|A Love Song]]\n | single2date = October 4, 1982\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Love Will Turn You Around''''' is the thirteenth studio album by [[Kenny Rogers]], released in 1982.\n\nThe title cut was the debut single and charted well, reaching #1 on the U.S. and Canadian country charts and adult contemporary charts, and #13 on the Hot 100 chart.  The other single, \"A Love Song\", didn't fare as well, only reaching #47 on the Billboard Hot 100. It was, however, #1 in Canada and #3 on the U.S. Country chart.\n\nThe album peaked at #34 on the Billboard 200 charts.  The album has been certified Platinum in both the U.S. and Canada.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n|title1 = [[Love Will Turn You Around (song)|Love Will Turn You Around]]\n|writer1 = Kenny Rogers, [[David Malloy]], Even Stevens, [[Thom Schuyler]]\n|length1 = 3:41\n|title2 = [[A Love Song (Lee Greenwood song)|A Love Song]]\n|writer2 = [[Lee Greenwood]]\n|length2 = 3:17\n|title3 = Fightin' Fire with Fire\n|writer3 = Bobby Harden\n|length3 = 2:33\n|title4 = Maybe You Should Know\n|writer4 = Peter McCann\n|length4 = 2:39\n|title5 = Somewhere Between Lovers and Friends\n|writer5 = [[Brent Maher]], [[Randy Goodrum]]\n|length5 = 2:55\n|title6 = Take This Heart\n|writer6 = J. P. Pennington\n|length6 = 3:24\n|title7 = If You Can Lie a Little Bit\n|writer7 = Bob Stone\n|length7 = 3:36\n|title8 = I'll Take Care of You\n|writer8 = [[J. D. Souther]]\n|length8 = 2:39\n|title9 = The Fool in Me\n|writer9 = [[Dave Loggins]], Randy Goodrum\n|length9 = 4:07\n|title10 = I Want a Son\n|writer10 = [[Steve Dorff]], [[Marty Panzer]]\n|length10 = 3:09\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n* Kenny Rogers \u2013 lead vocals, backing vocals (3), vocal arrangements, rhythm arrangements \n* Randy McCormick \u2013 keyboards (1)\n* Joel Scott \u2013 [[Rhodes piano|Fender Rhodes]] (2)\n* John Hobbs \u2013 acoustic piano (3), organ (7), organ solo (7)\n* Clarence McDonald \u2013 Fender Rhodes (4, 9, 10)\n* [[Billy Preston]] \u2013 organ (4)\n* [[Lincoln Mayorga]] \u2013 acoustic piano (4, 10)\n* [[Randy Goodrum]] \u2013 keyboards (5), rhythm arrangements (5)\n* [[Shane Keister]] \u2013 keyboards (5)\n* Eugene Golden \u2013 acoustic piano (6)\n* Steve Goldstein \u2013 acoustic piano (8)\n* [[Billy Joe Walker Jr.]] \u2013 guitar (1), acoustic guitar (2, 9), mandolin (2)\n* [[Fred Tackett]] \u2013 acoustic guitar (2, 4, 10), guitar (3, 9), electric guitar (7)\n* [[Paul Jackson Jr.]] \u2013 electric guitar (4, 6, 7, 9, 10)\n* [[Larry Byrom]] \u2013 guitar (5)\n* Jon Goin \u2013 guitar (5)\n* Randy Dorman \u2013 guitar (6)\n* [[Richie Zito]] \u2013 electric guitar (7), guitar solo (7)\n* [[Waddy Wachtel]] \u2013 acoustic guitar (8)\n* [[Josh Leo]] \u2013 electric guitar (8)\n* [[Joe Chemay]] \u2013 bass (1, 7, 9), backing vocals (6, 7)\n* [[Nathan East]] \u2013 bass (2, 4, 10)\n* [[Emory Gordy Jr.]] \u2013 bass (3)\n* Jack Williams \u2013 bass (5)\n* Chuck Jacobs \u2013 bass (6)\n* Bryan Garofalo \u2013 bass (8)\n* [[Paul Leim]] \u2013 percussion (1), drums (2,